    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="610"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P.W./5–1545</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-15">May 15,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: Following a meeting on May 12 between
                    the Secretary of Navy, Mr. McCloy,<note n="32" xml:id="d610fn32">John J. McCloy,
                        Assistant Secretary of War.</note> and Ambassador Harriman to consider
                    political implications of the expected Soviet entry in the Far Eastern war, the
                    attached memorandum<note n="33" xml:id="d610fn33">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> at the request of the War and Navy Departments was sent by me to
                    Secretaries Stimson and Forrestal. We are awaiting their replies before holding
                    another meeting with Ambassador Harriman prior to his return to Moscow. I will,
                    of course, keep you informed of any further developments on this subject.</p>
                <p>I understand that you discussed this general matter with Ambassador Harriman
                    before he left San Francisco.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph</hi> C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
